# AudioPlaybackSystem

## Purpose
Drives the audio device from App requests. On the first frame it lazily creates
`AudioDeviceSingletonComponent` (holding the platform `AudioDevice`) and returns. Once the device
exists, each frame it: applies the current category volumes to all voices, processes stop/pause/resume
requests, then play requests (looking the clip up in `ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_SoundMap` and
using the caller-assigned voice handle), and finally reaps finished voices via `AudioDevice::Update()`.
Play requests for an unknown clip UUID are ignored. Volumes default to 1.0 while
`AudioVolumeSingletonComponent` is absent.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| AudioDeviceSingletonComponent | read | Presence-check + access to the device; created lazily on the first frame |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Resolves `m_ClipID` to a `SoundClip` via `m_SoundMap` |
| AudioVolumeSingletonComponent | read | Current master/sound/music volumes; absent → defaults of 1.0 |
| PlayAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | read | clip id, voice id, category, loop, volume |
| StopAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | read | voice id to stop |
| PauseAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | read | voice id to pause |
| ResumeAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | read | voice id to resume |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| AudioDeviceSingletonComponent | add (deferred) | Created once on the first frame; holds the platform audio device that playback is driven through |
